The paper deals with the theory of evolutionary computation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves analyzing algorithms for optimization problems, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses mutation rates, which is a concept commonly used in neural networks and genetic algorithms, both of which fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also deals with optimizing run times, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
